        <name>state</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_vcp_vol_ctlr_cb::state</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Callback function for Volume Control Profile volume state. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Called when the value is remotely read as the Volume Controller. Called if the value is changed by either the Volume Renderer or Volume Controller, and notified to the to Volume Controller.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>vol_ctlr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Volume Controller instance pointer. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>err</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Error value. 0 on success, GATT error on positive value or errno on negative value. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>volume</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The volume of the Volume Renderer. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mute</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The mute setting of the Volume Renderer. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
